[1] 3) Checking homogeneity of variance assumption
[1] This can be checked using the Levene’s test:
# A tibble: 1 × 4
    df1   df2 statistic      p
  <int> <int>     <dbl>  <dbl>
1     2   189      4.06 0.0188
[1] The Levene’s test is not significant (p > 0.0188378453337873). Therefore, we can assume the homogeneity of variances in the different groups.
